    <text xml:id="t1">
        <body xml:id="t1-body">
            <pb n="1" facs="#rb071a" xml:id="t1-body-pb1"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" ref="#BIR" key="BIR">BIR ET MALER</name>
                    <lb/>
                    <date when="1916-06-17">17. June 1916</date>
                </dateline>
                <lb/>
                <lb/>
                <salute>My dearest 
                    <name type="person" ref="#MGB" key="MGB">Maud</name>:
                </salute>
            </opener>
                 <p>
                     No letters from
                     <lb/>
                     you for a long time, something
                     <lb/>
                     has gone radically wrong with
                     <lb/>
                     the mail lately. Expect I 
                     <lb/>
                     shall get a whole batch shortly.
                     <lb/>
                     Hope so.
                 </p>
                 <p>
                     I hear the Compulsion
                     <lb/>
                     Bill has passed the House, about
                     <lb/>
                     time too. I have not see the
                     <lb/>
                     provisions but I understand
                     <lb/>
                     they are fairly sweeping. It is
                     <lb/>
                     about time they did it.
                 </p>
                 <p>
                     By Jove the heat here
                     <lb/>
                     is getting appalling, horses and 
                     <lb/>
                     men are suffering. Personally
                     <lb/>
                     I am thin but fairly fit, fitter
                     <lb/>
                     than most I think, but one can
    
            <pb n="2" facs="#rb071b" xml:id="t1-body-x4-pb1"/>
                      
                      never tell from day to day
                     <lb/>
                      what tricks the sun will play.
                 </p>
                 <p>
                     I believe we are going back
                     <lb/>
                     for a rest shortly (we need it)
                     <lb/>
                     and I hope to get to <name type="place" ref="#ALX" key="ALX">Alexandria</name>
                     <lb/>
                     for a few days sea bathing.
                 </p>
                <p>
                    Had a priceless letter from
                    <lb/>
                    <name type="person" ref="#AND" key="AND">Andrews</name> from <name type="place" ref="#FRA" key="FRA">France</name> the other
                    <lb/>
                    day, I wish you could see it,
                    <lb/>
                    his adventures in <name type="place" ref="#PAR" key="PAR">Paris</name> are little
                    <lb/>
                    gems. He got 8 days leave to
                    <lb/>
                    <name type="place" ref="#LON" key="LON">London</name>, and by an extraordinary
                    <lb/>
                    coincidence his wife's leave
                    <lb/>
                    commenced the day he arrived.
                    <lb/>
                    They had a great time together
                    <lb/>
                    sight seeing etc. Lucky devil.
                    <lb/>
                    This old war owes you &amp; I a
                    <lb/>
                    holiday now I think: What
                    <lb/>
                    say you?
                </p>
            <pb n="3" facs="#rb071c" xml:id="t1-body-pb2"/>
                <p>
                    When I go to <name type="place" ref="#ALX" key="ALX">Alexandria</name>, I
                    <lb/>
                    am going to make enquiries 
                    <lb/>
                    about things, and how would
                    <lb/>
                    you like say a month in <name type="place" ref="#EGY" key="EGY">Egypt</name>
                    <lb/>
                    about Christmas time. Of course
                    <lb/>
                    it is all in the air, we may
                    <lb/>
                    not be here, and it may be
                    <lb/>
                    too hopelessly expensive, but it
                    <lb/>
                    is worth enquiring into anyway.
                    <lb/>
                    Don't build on it anyway, and 
                    <lb/>
                    the you won't be disappointed.
                    <lb/>
                    Poor little <name type="person" ref="#HEB" key="HEB">Helen</name> would, I am
                    <lb/>
                    afraid have to stay behind.
                    <lb/>
                    Perhaps anyway I may get to
                    <lb/>
                    <name type="place" ref="#NZE" key="NZE">N.Z.</name> before then, I understand
                    <lb/>
                    efforts are being made to get
                    <lb/>
                    some of the Main Body back for
                    <lb/>
                    a spell.
                </p>
                <p>So <name type="person" ref="#KIL">Kilcheuer</name> was caught,
            
            <pb n="4" facs="#rb071d" xml:id="t1-body-x8-pb1"/>
                    
                    well, their spy system is good.
                    <lb/>
                    It was given to him what is
                    <lb/>
                    only given to a few, that is to
                    <lb/>
                    die at the height of his fame,
                    <lb/>
                    and bearing arms in his 
                    <lb/>
                    profession. His career began late.
                    <lb/>
                    Once day at the Club at <name type="place" ref="#LIM" key="LIM">Limassol</name>
                    <lb/>
                    in <name type="place" ref="#CYP" key="CYP">Cyprus</name>, he threw his can &amp;
                    <lb/>
                    gloves on the table and exclaimed
                    <lb/>
                    "Thirty two and only a d----d
                    <lb/>
                    subaltern"
                </p>
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        So long old girl, next year
                        <lb/>
                            I think will be a happier one
                        <lb/>
                            for everybody.
                       <lb/>
                        <lb/>
                            God bless you both
                        
                    </salute>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed rend="u">
                        <name type="person" ref="#RTB">Roy</name>.
                    </signed>
                </closer>
        </body>
